There are many types of transition effects you can use in CSS! Here are a few examples:

1. `transition: opacity 1s;` - This will create a fade-in or fade-out effect by animating the `opacity` property.

2. `transition: transform 1s;` - This will animate the `transform` property and allow you to create different animation effects such as rotation, scaling, and translations.

3. `transition: background-color 1s;` - This will animate the `background-color` property and allow you to create a smooth color transition effect.

4. `transition: border 1s;` - This will animate the `border` property and allow you to create a border transition effect.

5. `transition: box-shadow 1s;` - This will animate the `box-shadow` property and allow you to create a shadow transition effect.

You can use these transition effects by adding the `transition` property to the element you wish to animate and specifying the desired property and duration. For example, to apply the `opacity` transition effect over a duration of 1 second, you can use the following code:

```
.element {
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 1s;
}

.element:hover {
  opacity: 1;
}
```

In this code, when you hover over the `.element` element, it will change its `opacity` property from 0 to 1 over a duration of 1 second due to the transition effect specified.

