}
```

In this code, when you hover over the `.element` element, it will change its `transform` property from `scale(1)` to `scale(1.5)` over a duration of 1 second due to the transition effect specified. This will have the effect of zooming in on the element. You can adjust the value of the `scale` function to change the level of zoom.

You can apply a zoom effect with the `transform` property within a transition effect that applies to other properties, such as the `background-color` and `color` properties. Here's an example:

