You can use the `useNavigation` hook from the `@react-navigation/native` package to navigate to the authentication screen after the user successfully registers. Here's an updated `handleRegistration` function that adds the navigation logic:

```
import { useNavigation } from '@react-navigation/native';

...

const handleRegistration = () => {
  if (
    name === '' ||
    surname === '' ||
    email === '' ||
    phone === '' ||
    password === '' ||
    confirmPassword === ''
  ) {
    Alert.alert('Ошибка!', 'Пожалуйста, заполните все поля для регистрации');
    return;
  }
  if (password !== confirmPassword) {
    Alert.alert('Ошибка!', 'Пароли не совпадают');
    return;
  }
  firebase
    .auth()
    .createUserWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
    .then((result) => {
      const userDetails = {
        name,
        surname,
        email,
        phone,
      };
      firebase.database().ref(`users/${result.user.uid}`).set(userDetails);

      // Navigation logic
      const navigation = useNavigation();
      navigation.navigate('Auth');
    });
};
```

Make sure to import the `useNavigation` hook at the top of your file:

```
import { useNavigation } from '@react-navigation/native';
``` 

Also, update the `navigation.navigate` call to match the name of your authentication screen.

No, it's best not to create redirects within `handleRegistration`. Instead, you can `return` a Promise from `handleRegistration` that resolves with the user data or rejects with an error message.

Then, you can call `handleRegistration`, wait for the Promise to resolve or reject, and redirect the user based on the result.

Here's an updated version of `handleRegistration`:

```
const handleRegistration = () => {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    if (
      name === '' ||
      surname === '' ||
      email === '' ||
      phone === '' ||
      password === '' ||
      confirmPassword === ''
    ) {
      reject('Пожалуйста, заполните все поля для регистрации');
      return;
    }
    if (password !== confirmPassword) {
      reject('Пароли не совпадают');
      return;
    }
    firebase
      .auth()
      .createUserWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
      .then((result) => {
        const userDetails = {
          name,
          surname,
          email,
          phone,
        };
        firebase.database().ref(`users/${result.user.uid}`).set(userDetails);
        resolve(userDetails);
      })
      .catch((error) => {
        reject(error.message);
      });
  });
};
```

Then, in your component, you can use `handleRegistration` and navigate based on the Promise result like so:

```
const onPressRegistration = async () => {
  try {
    const userDetails = await handleRegistration();
    navigation.navigate('Auth');
  } catch (error) {
    Alert.alert('Ошибка!', error);
  }
};

